page.title: 09CONSERVATION
page.content: This Summer the weather has not been very good at all.There has been a lot of thunder and lighting.But on Monday afternoons the weather has been pretty good (lucky for us because it is swimming).On mid and late June the weather has been nice to us aswell. We have a Conservation area at our School,we do not touch it.We leave it for the butterflies,other insects and the birds.Pheasants nest in our Conservation area aswell.We have a stream at the end of the conservation area.There are lots of frogs,toads,tadpoles and newts in it.The trees include :Oak,Ash,Willow and Hazel.We hope there will be some nuts for the Squirrels.We have a lot of Daffodils this Spring.We have a fence around the area.Sometimes we have a lot of rain and the stream overflows.
